Flag of Venezuela*
country Bolivaran Republic of Venezuela
used by Venezuela
from 12 March 2006
until Present
created by Bolivarian Government of Venezuela
format 2:3
shape rectangular
colours yellow, blu, red

flag has 3 horizontal stripes

other characteristics A horizontal tricolor of yellow, blue and red with the National Coat of Arms on the upper hoist-side of the yellow band and an arc of eight white five-pointed stars centered on the blue band.
Date 12 March 2006-present
